						<summary>

						<p>Three stones built into the east wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine, Vaidyanāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 15: 986 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. Seems to record a sale of land by the <hi rend="italic">mahāsabhā</hi> of Vikramābharaṇachaturvēdimaṅgalam to <hi rend="italic">Vīraśōḻaterinda-kaikkōḷār</hi> for being endowed to the temple for providing food offerings to the god. The inscription also gives the names of <hi rend="italic">āḷuṅgaṇattars</hi> probably of Vikramābharaṇa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam.</p>						

						</summary>
